ADDITIONAL NOTICE — Interoperability Research

Copyright (c) 2026 mediaporter contributors

This project is the result of independent interoperability research into
Apple's ATC (AirTrafficControl) media sync protocol, conducted under the
provisions of DMCA Section 1201(f) and the EU Directive 2009/24/EC
Article 6, for the sole purpose of enabling users to transfer their own
media files to their own iOS devices.

Certain protocol constants and cryptographic components included in this
project were derived from publicly available open-source repositories on
GitHub and are redistributed here for research and interoperability
purposes only. These components include:

  - An 84-byte host authentication blob, observed in multiple public
    implementations of the same protocol
  - A signature engine (CIG), based on publicly available source code

References to prior public work:
  - yinyajiang/go-tunes (GitHub) — Go implementation of the sync protocol
  - Kerrbty/IpaInstall (GitHub, Apache 2.0) — alternative protocol implementation
  - libimobiledevice project — foundational iOS protocol research

This software is intended exclusively for legitimate personal use:
transferring media you own to devices you own. It does not enable piracy,
circumvent content protection (DRM), or access copyrighted material.

See the docs/ directory for full research methodology, protocol analysis,
and reverse engineering documentation.
